07/06/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- EU security chief Javier Solana arrives Monday (7 June) in Kosovo to assess the fulfillment of international standards before Kosovo's final status is discussed. 
He is expected to call on local authorities to step up the process of implementing the standards. 
The EU has expressed a general concern that reforms in the province are losing steam.
On Sunday meanwhile, hundreds of Serbs gathered in Gracanica to protest the killing of a 17-year-old boy. 
They called for an end to violence against Serbs. 
Dimitrije Popovic was gunned down Saturday while waiting at a fast food stand. 
Two ethnic Albanians have been arrested. 
(The Independent - 07/06/04; B92, Beta, AP - 06/06/04)
